33
00:04:09,009 --> 00:04:14,794
We have to go to school. We have to spend nights up. We have to take tests.

34
00:04:14,794 --> 00:04:19,763
We have to flunk a few times and struggle. 

35
00:04:19,763 --> 00:04:28,033
And this is for a job that will last 20 years, will last nothing, will last zero mathematically. 

36
00:04:28,033 --> 00:04:32,689
Cause if you compare any number divided by infinity, you have zero. 

37
00:04:32,689 --> 00:04:39,197
Even if you go to this university of Arizona to get a degree to be an engineer, 

38
00:04:39,197 --> 00:04:42,722
you get a job for a thousand years, let's say, 

39
00:04:42,722 --> 00:04:45,700
That's zero. 

40
00:04:45,700 --> 00:04:50,470
When you come here, you are applying for the best position for eternity. 

41
00:04:50,470 --> 00:04:53,241
Therefore, the test is not easy. 

42
00:04:53,241 --> 00:04:57,610
It is not easy to accomplish that test. 

43
00:05:03,251 --> 00:05:06,310
I don't wanna miss anything because the question is very important. 

44
00:05:06,310 --> 00:05:10,257
"Why make the announcement that Rashad is a messenger of God?"

45
00:05:10,257 --> 00:05:13,720
"And why dwell on it?"

46
00:05:13,720 --> 00:05:17,751
Well, first of all, it's not my idea. 

47
00:05:17,751 --> 00:05:22,436
As you know, I tried to evade it for eight years. 

48
00:05:22,436 --> 00:05:25,562
because it's not easy for me either. 

49
00:05:25,562 --> 00:05:29,774
And I did not make the announcement until I was fired. 

50
00:05:29,774 --> 00:05:35,821
And I was scared to death. And I cried. I cried as I never did in my life. 

51
00:05:35,821 --> 00:05:41,329
So, I was thrown into it, into this announcement. 

52
00:05:44,770 --> 00:05:50,474
"Why can't we just worship God alone and forget about the messenger, the messengership?"

53
00:05:50,474 --> 00:05:52,710
"What's wrong with that?"

54
00:05:52,710 --> 00:05:58,465
You see, belief in God implies believing God and what God says. 

55
00:05:58,465 --> 00:06:05,296
If you believe in God, and you worship God alone, this means you believe everything that God says. 

56
00:06:05,296 --> 00:06:10,657
And God says in the Quran, I am sending... I have angels. There are angels. 

57
00:06:10,657 --> 00:06:17,124
If God says there are angels and we believe in God, then we must believe that there are angels. 

58
00:06:17,124 --> 00:06:21,849
God says "I sent down scriptures."

59
00:06:21,849 --> 00:06:26,355
And if you... if we believe in God, you believe that God sent scriptures. 

60
00:06:26,355 --> 00:06:29,813
And God said "He is sending messengers." 

61
00:06:29,813 --> 00:06:34,281
Then, you must believe what God says, that He sent messengers. 

62
00:06:34,281 --> 00:06:37,914
God said "I sent Moses." Then, we must believe that. 

63
00:06:37,914 --> 00:06:41,849
Because if we believe God, we have to believe God, what God is saying. 

64
00:06:41,849 --> 00:06:44,199
God said "I sent Jesus." 

65
00:06:44,199 --> 00:06:48,315
This means we have to believe that Jesus is a messenger of God. 

66
00:06:48,315 --> 00:06:53,461
And we see this in verse 285 of Sura 2:

67
00:06:53,461 --> 00:07:02,784
God says "the messenger and the believers believe in God, His angels, His scriptures and His messengers." 

68
00:07:02,784 --> 00:07:06,697
This does not violate the principle of worshiping God alone. 

69
00:07:06,697 --> 00:07:11,359
On the contrary, it affirms it. 

70
00:07:11,359 --> 00:07:12,564
Because, if you believe...

71
00:07:12,564 --> 00:07:17,327
You cannot say, I'm gonna worship God alone but I don't believe everything He says. 

72
00:07:17,327 --> 00:07:21,146
You have to believe what God says. 

73
00:07:29,006 --> 00:07:35,388
God said that Muhammad was the last prophet, the last message-bearing messenger, 

74
00:07:35,388 --> 00:07:36,808
but not the last messenger. 

75
